The paper discusses the development of a convolutional neural network (CNN) to identify contaminating material in residential recycling and compost bins using images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the authors mention the use of machine learning techniques such as CNNs, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in identifying contaminants in recycling and compost bins. The authors mention the use of deep learning techniques to train the model, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of image retrieval techniques to identify contaminants in recycling and compost bins, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
